snippet: A late winter storm blanketed the mid-Atlantic on Thursday after zipping across much of the South, leaving cars stranded on highways in Kentucky and 85,000 customers without power in West Virginia.
abstract: Late winter storm blankets mid-Atlantic region in snow, stranding hundreds of vehicles on highways in Kentucky and leaving 85,000 customers without power in West Virgina.
lead_paragraph: A late winter storm blanketed the mid-Atlantic on Thursday after zipping across much of the South, leaving cars stranded on highways in Kentucky and 85,000 customers without power in West Virginia.

headline.main: Snowstorm Strands Drivers and Knocks Out Power to Thousands
